summary: wow this had been a really emotional day...
title: wow this had been a really emotional day...
body:
BTS and Twice deserve so much love, I hope that despite all the hardships they face, they’ll grow and become happier as the years pass. 

They both are such great groups with really good music, Jihyo made me cry today, I can’t watch people I love tremble when they speak, it’s such an honor to be a part of their fandom. as for Hoseok… God Hoseok, this is the first time I’ve really seen such strong emotions reflect on someone’s face, it’s so beautiful seeing the fruit of such hard-work and pain and love and happiness all in one facial expression. 

When I talk and show people what i like about Kpop or Kpop artists to people it’s mostly very external in the sense of how the music sounds, their looks, and some of their achievements, but I reprimand myself now for not speaking of the inspiration, the energy, the motivation they produce in people, there’s so much more to liking these groups than just enjoying how they look on a stage, there’s passion mixed into messages, and these messages are spread to the youth of this generation, people and I all over the world, to anyone who’s ready to listen. Perhaps this is why I get so much pride from seeing their achievements. Even if they didn’t have a certain or clear message to deliver, or if all the songs were cheerful or about love and didn’t seem important, there is still a lesson to who’s willing to get inspiration, creativity, this is how humans function, we can make almost anything into something, and grow from our experiences and the experiences of others. 

I can’t wait to see what’s yet to come.

They both are such great groups with really good music, Jihyo made me cry today, I can’t watch people I love tremble when they speak, it’s such an honor to be a part of their fandom. as for Hoseok… God Hoseok, this is the first time I’ve really seen such strong emotions reflect on someone’s face, it’s so beautiful seeing the fruit of such hard-work and pain and love and happiness all in one facial expression. 

When I talk and show people what i like about Kpop or Kpop artists to people it’s mostly very external in the sense of how the music sounds, their looks, and some of their achievements, but I reprimand myself now for not speaking of the inspiration, the energy, the motivation they produce in people, there’s so much more to liking these groups than just enjoying how they look on a stage, there’s passion mixed into messages, and these messages are spread to the youth of this generation, people and I all over the world, to anyone who’s ready to listen. Perhaps this is why I get so much pride from seeing their achievements. Even if they didn’t have a certain or clear message to deliver, or if all the songs were cheerful or about love and didn’t seem important, there is still a lesson to who’s willing to get inspiration, creativity, this is how humans function, we can make almost anything into something, and grow from our experiences and the experiences of others. 

I can’t wait to see what’s yet to come.
